The paper discusses information retrieval models, which is a topic that falls under the category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also mentions the use of Bayesian networks and possibilistic models, which are both topics that fall under the categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the fuzziness of natural language, which is a topic that falls under the category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper proposes a hybridization of the two models, which is a topic that falls under the category of Soft Computing (cs.SI).
